The paper deals with stochastic resource allocation problems and proposes a machine learning approach using Markov decision processes and approximate dynamic programming methods. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of control policies and optimization techniques also indicates that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of hash tables and support vector regression, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
